# Node.js Keyboard Event Logger

## Description
This project captures Linux keyboard events using Node.js and emits them using EventEmitter.

## Features
- Reads raw keyboard input from /dev/input
- Emits keydown, keyup, keypress events
- Lightweight and dependency-free

## Usage

```js
const Keyboard = require('./index');
const kb = new Keyboard('event0');

kb.on('keydown', e => console.log('DOWN:', e));
kb.on('keyup', e => console.log('UP:', e));
kb.on('keypress', e => console.log('PRESS:', e));
kb.on('error', console.error);
